INFLUENCER Tshepi Vundla and rapper JR have welcomed a new little baby girl into the world. Tshepi posted the news on social media with a photo of herself and the baby, captioned with the baby’s birth date, 14 January. Industry peers Kayise Ngqula, Loot Love, Shudufhadzo Musida, Boity Thulo, Bontle Modiselle and others congratulated Tshepi on the arrival of her second baby. She and JR already have a four-year-old son, Siba. Media mogul Basetsana Khumalo said she hoped their baby brought them bliss. ALSO READ : BRENDEN PRAISE AND MPOOMY LEDWABA CELEBRATE FIVE YEARS OF MARRIAGE! “I promise I’m not crying. Congratulations, Tshepi. What joy! May your precious princess bring you and your beautiful family endless days of pure bliss. May the hand of God always be upon her all the days of her life. My heart is leaping for joy,” she said. Actress Zenande Mfenyana wrote: “Congratulations, Mama TV. Jonga! I’m here for this hair.” Model Siya Xaba also congratulated her. “Yaaaaay!!!! you did it!!!! Congratulations, Tshepi. Welcome, princess,” he wrote. Tshepi announced her pregnancy in November and the gender of their baby last month. “No matter what, I want my children to know they were wished for, longed for, prayed for, and that they are forever loved. We cannot wait to meet you,” she said when announcing her pregnancy. A post shared by Tshepi Vundla (@tshepivundla) 